Jerry Paul Keller (born June 20, 1937) is an American pop singer and songwriter.
Born in Fort Smith, Arkansas, Keller moved with his family to Tulsa, Oklahoma, when he was aged six, and Keller attended Tulsa's Will Rogers High School, graduating in 1955.
